			<h2>
				<a href="https://blog.gitea.io/2019/04/gitea-1.8.0-is-released/">
					Gitea 1.8.0 is released
				</a>
			</h2>
			<p>
				<i>Sun Apr 21, 2019</i>
				by
				<b>
					<a href="https://github.com/zeripath">
						zeripath
					</a>
				</b>
			</p>

			<p>The time has come for another major release! We are proud to present Gitea
1.8.0 to the world. <strong>This release contains two new security fixes which cannot be backported to the 1.7.0 branch, so it is recommended to update to this version.</strong>
In this release, we merged
<a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pulls?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;q=is:pr+milestone:1.8.0+is:merged">245 pull requests</a>
&ndash; This is more than 1.7.0 (157) and 1.6.0 (178).</p>
<p>You can download one of our pre-built binaries from our
<a href="https://dl.gitea.io/gitea/1.8.0/">downloads page</a> - make sure to select the
correct platform! For further details on how to install, follow our
<a href="https://docs.gitea.io/en-us/install-from-binary/">installation guide</a>. Unfortunately
there is a known issue with our prebuilt images on armv7, see <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/issues/6700">#6700</a>.</p>
<p>We&rsquo;d like to thank all of our backers on
<a href="https://opencollective.com/gitea">Open Collective</a>, who are helping us deliver
a better piece of software.</p>
<p>With that out of the way, here&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s new in Gitea version 1.8.0:</p>
<h2 id="oauth2-provider-5378httpsgithubcomgo-giteagiteapull5378">OAuth2 Provider <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pull/5378">#5378</a></h2>
<p>Gitea is now an <a href="https://docs.gitea.io/en-us/oauth2-provider/">OAuth2 Provider</a>. This fixes and closes issue <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/issues/27">#27</a>!</p>
<p><img src="https://docs.gitea.io/authorize.png" alt="Authorize TestApp Access"></p>
<p><em>Thanks to <a href="https://github.com/jonasfranz"><strong>@jonasfranz</strong></a></em></p>
<h2 id="repositories-can-now-be-archived-5009httpsgithubcomgo-giteagiteapull5009">Repositories can now be archived <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pull/5009">#5009</a></h2>
<p>Repositories in Gitea can now be archived. This prevents the creation of new issues,
pull-requests or pushing to the git repository.</p>
<p><img src="/demos/5009/1.png" alt="Archived Repository"></p>
<p><img src="/demos/5009/2.png" alt="Archived Repository List"></p>
<p><em>Thanks to <a href="https://github.com/kolaente"><strong>@kolaente</strong></a></em></p>
<h2 id="private-and-internal-organizations-1763httpsgithubcomgo-giteagiteapull1763">Private and Internal Organizations <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pull/1763">#1763</a></h2>
<p>Organizations can now be set to be Public, Internal or Private. Repositories created in
internal organizations will only be visible to logged-in users. Private organizations will
only be visible to those who are members.</p>
<p><img src="/demos/1763/1.png" alt="Archived Repository List"></p>
<p><em>Thanks to <a href="https://github.com/techknowlogick"><strong>@techknowlogick</strong></a> &amp; <a href="https://github.com/dblk"><strong>@DblK</strong></a></em></p>
<h2 id="implement-conversation-lock-for-issue-comments-5073httpsgithubcomgo-giteagiteapull5073">Implement &ldquo;conversation lock&rdquo; for issue comments <a href="https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pull/5073">#5073</a></h2>
<p>Conversations can now be locked in similar way to Github.</p>
<p><img src="/demos/5073/1.png" alt="Locked Comments"></p>
<p><em>Thanks to <a href="https://github.com/adelowo"><strong>@adelowo</strong></a></em></p>
